  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: This package contains a synthetic weakener — the decision rationale treats the presence of a relative hemolysis index alarm threshold (RH < 1) as a sufficient safety condition, when in fact it is only a necessary condition for the broader safety goal of ensuring patient safety across all operating conditions.",
